<Author>Athens123
<Content>Excellent Hotel! We recently traveled to Mexico City and stayed at the Embassy Suites for approx. one week. We chose the hotel based on the reviews provided by fellow travellers and we were not disappointed.The hotel is located on Paseo de la Reforma (close to the Centro Historico and to Chapultepec). It is right at the Glorieta Colon, and the Turibus stops in front of it.The hotel is fairly new and is very clean and well maintained. The rooms are big, like a suite, nice big bathroom, tvs, kitchenette. You have everything you need in the room, but if you need anything else you can call the 24 hour service line and they will help you with whatever it is you need. The hotel offers a complimentary breakfast buffet which is very good and very complete. Evita restaurant is also a great Argentinean restaurant, and there is also a Starbucks right in the lobby. The pool and jacuzzi were located in the basement and they were a great spot to relax after being all day in the streets of Mexico City. The gym is also right there.The best feature of this hotel is its staff. They are very friendly and nice to their guests abd very accommodating. They are ready to help you out whenever you need it. We felt as they were treating us like family, and this was very nice! The concierges are also present at the hotel from early in the morning until late in the evening and they can guide and help you in a very good way. We have them book tours for us with the private guides of the hotel to the Basilica de Guadalupe and the Pyramids. The price was good and what you get for it is priceless. Ask for Mr Fernando Piro. He is an excellent guide and taxi driver, and he can take you whereever you need to go. We used the hotel taxi service quite a lot. They are very friendly and helpful, and are also very reliable and on time. If you travel alone this is an excellent way to feeling safe in Mexico City, although we never felt unsafe while visiting the city.The concierge also booked tours for us with a touring company called Estur. We took a day tour to Puebla and Cholula, and another to Cuernavaca and Taxco. Both tours were excellent, with very pleasant and knowledgeable tour guides who speak both Spanish and English.We also bought tickets to the Ballet Floklorico Nacional. We recommend it. Very nice!Conclusion: if you are traveling to Mexico City stay at the Embassy Suites. You won't regret it. We highly recommend it and next time we're in Mexico City we will stay there for sure! 
