<Author>enderart
<Content>Loved the Embassy suites We stayed at the Embassy Suites in July and where very happy that we did. The building is somewhat new, the suites are larger than average, with 2 large flat panel tvs in each room, the view was spectacular from the 17th floor; also a large pull out bed in the second room. The pool was pretty nice located in the basement of the hotel, so didn't have to worry about the rain or thunderstorms outside. The breakfast had a cook for made to order eggs, pancakes, fruit, cereal, some local flavor food (chilaquiles, quesadillas) which was delicious - so the breakfast was excellent. In the afternoon from 6-8pm. there was a hotel managers reception wherein you get free drinks, including tequila, wine, beer, chips, nuts, etc. which was great for meeting with associates prior to going out to town for dinner. Our first night, we tried their Argentinian Restaurant - Evita, it was more of international menu instead of Argentinian for authentic Argentinian you need to go to a restaurant called Cambalache and another is called La Mansion. The hotel is located on reforma, walking distance to the Monumento a la Revolucion and within 10 minutes in taxi to the Bellas Artes and 15 minutes to the Zocalo - Main Plaza of Mexico City in front of the Cathedral. If you are there on Sundays, the hotel will loan you a bicycle to ride in the Reforma Street which is closed for traffic on Sunday so people can rollerblade and ride bicycles with their families. The hotel staff was very friendly. The hotel does not have a self parking, so you have to use the valet and the driveway is somewhat cumbersome. Also, be careful with the local police you try to make a left turn into the hotel in the afternoons, so you will have to make a right turn, then another and another to get onto the street that goes in front of the hotel which by the way is located in front of the Christopher Columbus (Glorieta Colon) which in spanish is Cristobal Colon. We would definitely recommend this hotel and will definitely stay here again. 
