<Author>cyril1980
<Content>Best value ever -- excellent experience at a bargain I booked on the hotel website. This hotel only has suites. They are divided in three categories. I booked a lower-end suite on the basis of the net direct/advance payment rate of 143 dollars (i.e. around 97 euros at the time).And what did I get for this?Simply the best-value room I've ever seen. When we showed up at 7 in the morning they apologized that the room wasn't ready yet. The reception staff were very nice and smiling and efficient. So we left our bags there and explored Mexico City that morning. When we came back we got a top-floor corner suite of about 50 square metres including two huge flat-screen TVs, nice sofas and an excellent bed.The gym was small (about 5-6 machines plus about 4 cardio treadmills and bicycles) but clean and inviting, with lots of available towels, water and apples. The pool area was also very nice (although windowless and in the basement), with lots of chaises longues, excellent lighting and nice blue and gold mosaic.And the breakfast was amazing, with cooked-to-order eggs with lots of vegetable, cheese, bacon and toppings (plus lots of other sweet and salty stuff). Excellent service in the breakfast room too.I got the IHT delivered to my room every morning at 8 and when I asked for a power plug adaptor it took them about 30 seconds to deliver it at my door. And checking out took about 10 seconds.Ah, and the location is unbeatable, with Insurgentes metro station, Polanco and the city centre (Zocalo etc) all nearby (by Mexico City standards).Overall: a near-perfect experience. For 97 euros this was simply amazing. 
