<Author>normanfla
<Content>Great stay at the Embassy Suites We stayed at this hotel - Xmas week 12/25 thru 12/31. Chose hotel based on member reviews. Wow what a great hotel. It's a good 4 star , Doesn't have a fancy lobby or coffee shop but there were several outstanding features1) Room was Incredible. There were 3 of us - 2 adults - 1 teenager - She had her own ensuite room with HD TV . Ours was similar - very well appointed, huge room, marble everywhere.2) Staff were amazing - They all spoke great english and were unbelievably helpful - especiially the front desk and tour desk. I wish I could remember some of their names . when I read some reviews of other hotels, we really were fortunate to have such a great staff, that really went out of their way to help us.3) They have a great pool/execise area in the basement - it's spacious and beautiful.4) Breakfast - included in the room rate - was outstanding. They made the usual American eggs to order, but had a great choice of Mexican dishes as well. It's one of the best breakfasts I've had in years.5) There's a free happy hour with Hors d'oeuvres, They could do with redecorating the dining room/coffee shop - The munchies are pretty basic - mostly fried fillers.6) The rate was good - we paid about $110 a night for 3, with breakfast includedThere's an unbelievably expensive Agentinian steak house on the ground floor - as well as an equally expensive Starbucks.Overall the place is fantastic. - It's well located on the middle of the polanco. It's a pretty quiet , commercial section, but we used to walk to the city center /Zocolo each night after dark. We never felt worried, there were plenty of people and there were cops hanging out everywhere. Not sure I'd walk down some of the side streets - but the main street are fine.We loved MC. everybody in my office turns up their nose and says why would you go there' - We had a great week, the Mexican people were wonderful and there were some Wonderful places to visit - and we never got ill once !. 
