<Content>Great value and service We spent a week in Mexico City, six nights at the Embassy Suites and two at the Four Seasons. Can't say enough nice things about the E.S. The suite was big enough for the five of us (two adults, two teens and an almost teen). It was clean and well appointed (two flat panel tv's, mini-fridge, ironing board). The maid service came twice a day, cleaned in the morning, pulled out the sleeper sofa bed and turn down the other beds at night. They kept us stocked with bottled water (necessary in Mexico for those of us from up north). The workout room had a nice selection of equipment, with little towels and bottles of water on a side table. The pool and hot tub worked well with the kids. Between 6-8pm there is the manager's happy hour with free drinks and snacks. The staff was all very friendly and helpful. But the best part of the E.S. was the breakfast in the mornings. They have eggs made to order, two types of juice, lots of cut fruits, cereals, coffee, teas, pancakes, and more. The six nights we spend at the E.S. cost $1400ish US after taxes and the two at the Four Season cost $950 (because we had to have two rooms, maximum of three to a room). The F.S.price does not include breakfast or the occasional cocktail. When we go back to M.C, we are staying at the Embassy Suites. 
