<Content>Don't travel alot, but loved Embassy We needed to go to Mexico City to visit our daughter who is studying there. As infrequent and frugal travelers, we wanted a place that would be comfortable to return to after exploring the city . Embassy Suites was the right choice for our family. No matter what your budget(ours was tight), a person can find everything they need here. You can experience Mexican culture, but are able to find someone to help out in English when needed.  Enrique the concierge treated us as very well during our stay and was sensitive to our needs(not wanting to spend more than needed). He was also very upfront about what was okay to do and what wasn't. We felt very safe during our time in Mexico City...the people were wonderful.  Every single one of the staff was helpful, friendly and all about service excellence. The things that stood out for us were, the concierge service provided...from helping us rent a car, to calling a safe taxi for our daughter to take back to her school at night when needed, they were there; we used the washing machine/dryer several times during our stay; our older teen/early twenty-year olds loved the exercise room; the staff that allowed us to break a few small rules such as allowing our daughter to sleep over with us without creating a fuss; the breakfast service was out of this world;and the housekeepers did an excellent job as did room service. Jorge even arranged a larger car to take us to the airport when we left. It is doubtful we will ever be back to Mexico City, but if we did, this is where we would stay no questions asked. No one in our group became ill, but if we had, Embassy Suites would have been a piece of heaven to stay at. Our only regret is that we couldn't leave larger tips for the services provided. 
