<Author>CenturyClubMember
<Content>4 Seasons Quality-Suite Price I am not the type to gush about Suite Style Hotels. However, I must commend Embassy Suites for their new property in Mexico City. The hotel is well located on the Paseo de La Reforma and boasts a full service Starbucks in the lower lobby. The hotel is new( 6 months ?) and looks it. The highlights are the rooms.First you get two rooms for price of one. There were two flat screen LCD TV's ( 36 inch ?) in my suite. Marble in the bathroom. The beds were very comfy with similar linens,pillows etc that you would find at the Ritz or 4 Seasons. The staff was friendly and appeared happy to be there ! There was an excellent buffet breakfast included !All for $159/night plus tax !Negatives would include noisy AC and only one window in the suite. Also, the business center is small and cramped. The biggest minus is that you need to cab it to Polanco for most dining options.The hotel was a great value relative to other 4-5 star alternatives. A pleasant surprise ! 
