<Author>Zmel110
<Content>World Class Customer Service at Embassy Suites from a road warrior My 23 year old sister and my 15 year old brother were in Cancun when rumors of Hurricane Dean frightened us. There were no flights out and we did not want to risk it. So we got on a bus and drove 24 hours to mexico city!! We picked Embassy Suites because of the reviews on tripadvisor. We did not care much for Mexico city but we were blown away by the way we were treated by the hotel staff. I have never experienced customer service anywhere the way I experienced customer service at this hotel. After such a firghtening experience we felt right at home at this hotel. From the bell boy to the front desk staff were all fantastic. Hotel was very nice and clean. In fact, they came in while we were out in the afternoon and re-cleaned our room and un-did our bed so that we could easily go under the covers. This was a world class experience. I am a road warrior and I stay at a different hotel every week from Hyatt to Holiday Inn but I have never experienced such customer service before. And No, it was not more expensive. We booked our hotel for a Monday night(usually expensive) on a Saturday and it was $150/night and it was in the same range as the other hotels. Over all it was great. Thank you Embassy Suites. 
